text: Minneapolis City Council members postponed a vote Tuesday on Mayor Jacob Frey's choice for a location for a future Third Precinct police station.

meta.headline: Minneapolis City Council delays vote on Third Precinct police station

text: But Council Member Emily Koski, who led a group of council members in pushing for the delay, as well as a request for more information on the city's site selection thus far, disagreed, saying there was "still outstanding information" preventing the council from responsibly making a decision.

meta.headline: Minneapolis City Council delays vote on Third Precinct police station

text: Those in favor of the delay and request for more information by Oct. 31 included Koski and Council Members Elliott Payne, Robin Wonsley, Jeremiah Ellison, Jamal Osman, Jason Chavez and Aisha Chughtai.
